HEADWORD: Tellurhydric
<hw>Tel`lur*hy"dric</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Of, pertaining to, or designating, hydrogen telluride, which is
regarded as an acid, especially when in solution.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

